defaultFurther Example
default&#xa0;
defaultUK Coal Production Ltd operates a surface coal mine called Potland Burn near Ashington in Northumberland. The site commenced operations in 2010 and will extract 2.2 mi
defaultllion tonnes of coal over its five year life
default, in 2012 the site employed 96 people of whom 82% live within 15 miles of the site. As part of a signed Legal Agreement the company has contributed £500,000 into a local community fund which is used to promote co
defaultmmunity benefits and amenities. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAll the coal from site is transported by rail to English Power Stations and has a much lower Carbon Footprint from both excavation and delivery than imported coal.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe indigenous 
defaultcoal
default industry
default in the UK provides high quality jobs in rural or deprived areas, both directly employed in the mining operations but also in the supply chain and in particular the speci
defaultalist equipment and plant required, and the maintenance and small engineering and repair sector. The coal industry employed over 6,000 people in 2012 and despite the closure of Maltby and Daw Mill Collieries in 2013 and the suspension of operations at the 
defaultmajority of sites in Scotland there are 4,100 employees at the end of August 2013 which we expect to increase to in excess of 4,500 during the next six months as operations in Scotland re-start. 
default&#xa0;
defaultSupply chain jobs dependent on the coal mining sector are a
defaultround 15,000.
default&#xa0;
defaultMining consultants from UK based organisations are busy on coal and other mineral projects worldwide and particularly in India currently. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe 
defaultConsultancy services from the UK on mining projects are in high demand, and the fact that they are familiar with UK coal underground systems gives the competitive advan
defaulttage that the deep reserves worked here give unique experience, compared with some other coal deposits worldwide.
default&#xa0;
defaultUK manufacturers were involved at the start of the mechanisation programme which changed the face of underground coal production in the 
default1960’s and 1970’s. The continuing development and improvements made to this equipment as reserves became deeper again enhances the design and supply reputation of UK based companies.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultIn the coal sector
default,
default UK operations are all performed by UK based companies and very few have overseas interests. The presence of large mining compan
defaulties in London offices does not encourage them to use UK based suppliers
default,
default and most mining equipment supply is now done by large global corporations
default, notwithstanding that, the engineering design for these products is maintained in the UK but some of the manu
defaultfacturing has moved to China and USA.
