defaultSo far as Coalpro is aware there has been no contact to involve coal mining companies in discussion of the possibility of signing up to the EITI.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe regulatory framework in the UK currently ensures that all payments made to local and central movement in the form of fees, 
defaultbusiness rates and other 
defaulttaxes and contributions to 
defaultlocal infrastructure is
default done so in a fully transparent way
default,
default and the Group bel
defaultieves that there is no requirement
default for
default further regulation.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is noted from the press release dated 10
defaultth
default July 2013 posted on the EITI website that Business Minister Jo Swinson said 
default…..“Under the EITI, extractives companies operating in the UK would report
default material payments to the UK government, totalling billions of pounds, who will also report the receipts it received. The payments of tax, licence fees and other receipts will be disclosed in reports conforming to the EITI standards
default.
